Grilled Tahini Chicken
  --Jessica Battilana

3-4lb chickenm cut into 10 pieces
kosher salt
6 garlic cloves, peeled
2 tsp whole cumin seeds, toasted (or 2 1/2 tsp ground cumin)
2 tsp paprika
1/4 c tahini
1/4 c lemon juice
2 tbsp olive oil

Season the chicken pieces on both sides with salt, transfer to a plate or small baking pan, and refrigerate for at least 1 hr (or up to overnight). In a mortar and pestle, pouind the garlic to a paste with a pinch of salt. Add the cumin seeds and pound until ground, then transfer to a bowl and add the paprika, tahini, lemon juice, and olive oil. Season to taste with salt; it will haev the consistency of peanut butter. Remove the chicken from the refrigerator and slather the tahini marinade all over each piece. Cover loosely with plastic wrap and let stand until the chicken is at room temp (no more than 1 hr). Preheat a charcoal or gas grill for direct, medium high heat. grilling. When the grill is hot, put the chicken pieces on the grill skin side down, and cook until the skin begins to brown and you can easily lift the pieces off the grate. Continue to cook, turning frequently and moving the chicken from hot to cooler parts as needed, until cooked through,, ~25-30 min. The chicken has a tendency to stick, so be vigilent about turning. If it looks like it might burn before finishing, move to cooler section and cover, leaving vents open, until cooked through. 
